# Quantum Machine Learning: IBTrACS Classification

The end-to-end pipeline for classifying tropical cyclone severity has been implemented and successfully executed, fulfilling all the structural and algorithmic requirements of the project.

## Project Construction

The project was divided into a clear, modular architecture exactly as specified:

1. **[data_loader.py](file:///e:/Agentic-ai-research/Quantum-cyclone-implementation/src/data_loader.py)**: Downloads the IBTrACS v4 dataset from NOAA, filters for seasons 2004â€“2023, and extracts the 6 critical features: `WIND`, `PRES`, `LAT`, `LON`, `USA_RMW`, and `STORM_SPEED`.
2. **[preprocessing.py](file:///e:/Agentic-ai-research/Quantum-cyclone-implementation/src/preprocessing.py)**: Implements the required 3-class labelling (TS, MH, SH). It performs a robust 80/20 GroupShuffleSplit relying on the storm `SID` to prevent data leakage. The training set is subsampled to balance classes, following standardisation and domain rescaling $x \mapsto [0, \pi]$ based solely on training set statistics.
3. **[iqp_feature_map.py](file:///e:/Agentic-ai-research/Quantum-cyclone-implementation/src/iqp_feature_map.py)**: A manual, parameterless Instantaneous Quantum Polynomial circuit constructor implementing Hadamard layers, single-qubit $Z$-rotations ($R_Z(x_j)$), and fully-entangled Controlled-Phase gates ($CP(x_j \cdot x_k)$) parameterized by depth $L$.
4. **[quantum_kernels.py](file:///e:/Agentic-ai-research/Quantum-cyclone-implementation/src/quantum_kernels.py)**: Evaluates kernel functions $K_{ij} = |\langle\Phi(x_i)|\Phi(x_j)\rangle|^2$ via `AerSimulator(method='statevector')`. Includes baseline QSVM circuits ($Z$ and $ZZ$). To respect $\mathcal{O}(N^2)$ complexity, it evaluates explicitly over a balanced 600-sample quantum training subset.
5. **[classical_baselines.py](file:///e:/Agentic-ai-research/Quantum-cyclone-implementation/src/classical_baselines.py)**: Scikit-Learn pipelines wrapping `SVC` models. Uses 5-fold grid search cross-validation space over $C \in \{0.1, 1, 10, 100\}$ for QSVMs and Classical kernels (Linear, Poly-3, RBF).
6. **[evaluation.py](file:///e:/Agentic-ai-research/Quantum-cyclone-implementation/src/evaluation.py)**: Calculates multi-class accuracy, precision, recall, F1, Cohen's Kappa, normalized confusion matrices, and the Kernel-Target alignment score via Frobenius norms.
7. **[visualisation.py](file:///e:/Agentic-ai-research/Quantum-cyclone-implementation/src/visualisation.py)**: Output generators for the confusion matrix heatmap and circuit depth accuracy comparisons.
8. **[run_experiment.py](file:///e:/Agentic-ai-research/Quantum-cyclone-implementation/src/run_experiment.py)**: The main orchestrator traversing the end-to-end execution flow.

